## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **RevenueCat vs react-native-iap:** RevenueCat is recommended because it handles receipt validation server-side (preventing fraud), works across both stores, and has built-in subscription management for Phase 2. However, it requires creating a free RevenueCat account. Would you prefer to use the lower-level `react-native-iap` instead?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Phase 1 Scope Confirmation:** Should I implement Phase 1 only for now (trial + $6.99 purchase), keeping Phase 2 (AI/Convex/Clerk) as a documented plan for later? Or do you want both phases implemented now?

> [!WARNING]
> **Google Play Console Setup:** The $6.99 in-app product must be created manually in your Google Play Console before testing. I can guide you through this but cannot automate it. You will need a Google Play Developer account ($25 one-time fee).

## Open Questions

1. **Trial Length:** You mentioned 3 days. Is that confirmed, or would you prefer 7 days to give users more time to build habits?
2. **What happens during trial?** Should trial users have access to 100% of features, or should some features (like CSV Export) be locked behind the paywall even during trial?
3. **RevenueCat account:** Do you already have a RevenueCat account, or should the plan include setup steps?
4. **Phase 2 AI Provider:** Do you prefer OpenAI (GPT-4), Google Gemini, or Anthropic Claude for the AI coach?

## Verification Plan

### Phase 1 Verification

#### Automated Tests
- Build the app with `eas build -p android` and verify no crashes
- Test trial timer by manually setting `@gym_log_first_open` to a past date in AsyncStorage
- Test paywall appearance after trial expiry
- Test "Restore Purchase" flow

#### Manual Verification
- Install on a real Android device
- Verify trial banner appears and counts down correctly
- Verify paywall blocks the app after 3 days
- Test the $6.99 purchase flow using Google Play test tracks
- Verify "Restore Purchase" works after reinstall

### Phase 2 Verification
- Test Clerk sign-in flow (Google + Apple)
- Test local-to-cloud data migration (verify all workouts, PRs, measurements transfer)
- Test AI chat with sample questions
- Test subscription purchase and verify AI tab unlocks
- Test that Tier 1/2 users see no changes to their experience
